==Old English==
===Etymology===
From the Germanic, from Indo-European ''*wer-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[werpa]], Old Saxon [[werpan]] (Dutch [[werpen]]), Old High German [[werfan]] (German [[werfen]]), Old Norse [[verpa]] (Danish [[verpe]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐌹𐍂𐍀𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root also led to Latin [[verbera]], Old Slavic ''vr’ba'' (Russian [[верба]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'weorpan/

===Verb===
'''weorpan''' (strong verb class III: '''wearp''' ‘he threw’; '''wurpon''' ‘they threw’; '''ġeworpen''' ‘thrown’)
# to [[throw]], cast down

